---
---

<section class="faq-section">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 800px;">
    <div class="text-center mb-5">
      <div class="badge-container mb-3" style="display: inline-block; background-color: rgba(82, 206, 199, 0.12); border-radius: 50px; padding: 0.35rem 1.25rem; border: 1px solid rgba(82, 206, 199, 0.25);">
        <span style="font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600; color: #52CEC7; text-transform: uppercase;">Got Questions?</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h1">Frequently Asked Questions About Startup Engineering Pods</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-accordion">
      <!-- Question 1 -->
      <details class="faq-item" open>
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            What is an engineering pod?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          An engineering pod is a fixed-cost, fully-managed software team, typically a designer, developers, and a DevOps engineer working under one Tech Lead, that builds your product as a single unit, instead of you hiring and managing each specialist separately.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 2 -->
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            Why not hire freelancers?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          Freelancers work project-to-project with no shared accountability and no continuity if one leaves. A pod is a managed, cross-functional team with one Tech Lead responsible for delivery, so quality and timelines don't depend on any single person.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 3 -->
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            Why not build an in-house team?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          In-house hiring typically costs £25k+/month once you include salaries, tax, benefits, and recruitment fees, and takes 3-6 months to get a full team in place. A pod gives you the same disciplines (design, dev, DevOps, AI) for a flat fee from £2,500/month, live within 48 hours.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 4 -->
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            How quickly can we start?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          Most pods are onboarded and writing code within 48 hours of your application being approved.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 5 -->
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            Can you work with our existing developers?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          Yes. Our pods are modular and plug-and-play, whether you have a sole developer, a CTO who needs extra velocity, or a small team that lacks specialised DevOps or AI expertise. Our engineers integrate into your existing Git workflows, Slack channels, and Agile sprints.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 6 -->
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            What happens if we outgrow the pod?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          Outgrowing us is the goal. We support you through pre-seed and seed stages with clean, well-documented codebases and automated CI/CD pipelines, so when you raise your next round and hire in-house, we manage a seamless hand-off.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 7 -->
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            Are there long-term contracts?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          No. The subscription is flexible month-to-month, allowing you to scale up, scale down, or cancel at any time.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 8 -->
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            How much does a startup engineering pod cost?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          Plans start at £2,500/month on a flat-rate, all-inclusive basis, covering design, development, DevOps, and AI integration in one invoice.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 9 -->
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            Do you build AI agents and AI features for startups?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          Yes. AI & ML integration is included as standard, such as Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), autonomous AI agent workflows, and custom LLM training, alongside core product development.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Question 10 -->
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            Is this suitable for a non-technical founder?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          Yes. Many pod clients are non-technical founders. The dedicated Tech Lead handles technical decisions and reports progress in plain English through bi-weekly sprint updates.
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
